abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, June 8. A dispatch from Silver City, Idaho, states that about 40 hostile Bannock Indians are camped at Juniper Creek, 10 miles from South Mountain. They were discovered yesterday by a friendly Indian. Capt. Harper, who left here last night with 20 Home Guards, sent here this morning for reinforcements, which will be sent forward immediately. If these Bannocks remain where they are, Harper will certainly attack them to-night or to-morrow morning.
